name: Candy by Catch-22
description:
Spray painting on canvas 40-30 inch original one off unique piece.

Bio -

Inspired by everything from music to architecture, Catch-22 shatters the world he sees creating fractured portraits with shards of light and colour enveloping and piercing the figure! 
 Painted at Upfest in Bristol and sand sea and spray in Blackpool  two of the best urban art events in the UK. And has also recently been commissioned to paint and design his own illuminations alongside some huge urban artists including Inkie,  Osch,  Foundary, Agent Provoceteur, Neil Ennui and The Toasters.

name: Childs Play
description:
"Childs Play " By CizeOne 
3ft x 4ft .

CizeOne - Cizeone started his love affair with graffiti back in the early days of Hip Hop. Original influences were films such as Beat Street and Style wars in which the phenomenon of graffiti writing completed Cizeone in the belief that this art form would one day be recognised in all its clarity. Having completed big commissions for Tattoo conventions (a hundred foot long security wall) and Red Bull, Cizeone has finally started to push through his own unique style of  painting.
 
Early influences from comic books helped to create this style which is apparent with the mixed media that he uses. Cizeone's style has been compared with the infamous Vaughn Bode, which to Cizeone is regarded as an honour. More of his work can be found on his website Northkingz Design.
A chance to own a rare released unique piece by the man himself .

name: 'ghost one'  By Savant.
description:
Spraypaint on board, framed, 33.5 x 28.5 approx.

Savant bio :
Savant has been creating images for many years, producing zines and designing a street wear range along with painting, collages and placing stickers. His work explores the situationist aesthetic, commenting on the status quo using densely built collages and large spray painted pieces, on found or recycled boards and frames. Central to his work is an ongoing series of collage/sketch books, which act as starting points for his finished pieces. 
He has just finished his latest show ‘Abstract Theory’ and is contributing to ‘Heroes and Villains’ for Fitzrovia Noir, where, along with other street artists having work displayed on the wooden panels on the outside of the Bell pub in New Goulston Street, London.
